preference.name: TC_Undefined_Variant_State_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Determines if the undefined variant occurrence state is enabled. This state is indicated by the ? symbol. Valid Values: true - If any of the variant options in the variant condition is not set in the variant rule, the corresponding variant occurrence assumes an undefined (?) state. false - If any of the variant options in the variant condition is not set in the variant rule, the corresponding variant occurrence assumes a defined (Y) state.
